{"id":438556447,"lang":"java","time":"1 year, 1 month","timestamp":1609789599,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"4 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/438556447/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Integer to Roman","memory":"38.7 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    int[] values = {1000, 900, 500, 400, 100, 90, 50, 40, 10, 9, 5, 4, 1};    \nString[] symbols = {\"M\",\"CM\",\"D\",\"CD\",\"C\",\"XC\",\"L\",\"XL\",\"X\",\"IX\",\"V\",\"IV\",\"I\"};\n    public String intToRoman(int num) {\n        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();\n        \n        for (int i = 0; i < values.length && num > 0; i++) {\n            while (values[i] <= num) {\n                num -=values[i];\n                sb.append(symbols[i]);\n            }\n        }\n        return sb.toString();\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"integer-to-roman"}
